## 5. Clean-Room Development Process

Use this flow for every upstream-inspired feature.

```text
Clone upstream
  ↓
Read architecture
  ↓
Write notes
  ↓
Write UrgoOS feature spec
  ↓
Stop looking at source
  ↓
Implement from spec
  ↓
Add tests
  ↓
Document inspiration and license status
```

Never implement while directly referencing upstream code side-by-side unless intentionally vendoring with license compliance.

Recommended practice:

1. Research agent reads upstream and writes a spec.
2. Human or second agent reviews spec.
3. Execution agent implements from the spec only.
4. Production code is compared conceptually, not line-for-line.

