## 12. Tool Runtime and Safety Model

### 12.1 Tool risk levels

| Level | Examples | Approval |
|---|---|---|
| safe | calculator, time, memory search | no |
| read_only | read file, list dir, git diff | maybe configurable |
| approval_required | write file, run shell, network request | yes |
| dangerous | delete files, install packages, deploy | explicit yes |
| forbidden | credential exfiltration, malware, destructive hidden ops | never |

### 12.2 Initial tools

Build these first:

```text
memory.search
memory.write_candidate
memory.list
memory.invalidate

time.now
calculator.eval

file.list_dir
file.read
file.search_text

git.status
git.diff

shell.run_approved
```

Later:

```text
web.search
docs.ingest
project.index
workflow.start
workflow.resume
agent.delegate
```

### 12.3 Tool execution rule

The model should never directly execute tools. It should request a tool call. Urgo Core validates:

- tool exists
- schema is valid
- risk level
- path allowlist
- approval status
- command allowlist/denylist
- output redaction

Then the tool runtime executes.

