## 22. Security Boundaries

### 22.1 Secrets

Never store:

- API keys
- passwords
- private keys
- seed phrases
- OAuth tokens
- SSH keys
- session cookies

Add redaction patterns before event logging.

### 22.2 Filesystem

File tools must enforce:

- allowlisted root directories
- realpath checks
- no path traversal
- no hidden destructive writes
- no reading secrets by default

### 22.3 Shell

Shell tool default:

```env
URGO_TOOL_SHELL_ENABLED=false
```

When enabled:

- approval required
- command logged
- output logged with redaction
- denylist dangerous commands
- run in sandbox where possible

### 22.4 Memory safety

Memory must be:

- inspectable
- editable
- deletable
- invalidatable
- exportable

The user must always be able to see and correct what UrgoOS thinks it remembers.

